Godwin Isenyo, Kaduna Security officers were said to have repelled some gunmen suspected to be kidnappers along the Kaduna-Abuja Expressway on Friday afternoon. It was learnt that the officers, comprising the military and police, repelled the bandits who opened fire on motorists near Olam Feeds Company, a few kilometres away from Kaduna metropolis. The Kaduna State Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan, disclosed this to journalists at the scene of the incident. Some injured residents were first treated at Olam Feeds Clinic before being referred to a specialist hospital for better medical attention. Meanwhile, the state governor, Nasir El-Rufai, has commended the security agents when briefed on the development, according to the commissioner. El-Rufai was said to have praised the security officersÂ  for their courage and bravery in confrotting the kidnappers. Wishing the injured persons and motorists speedy recovery, the governor also praised medical workers at the clinic for stabilising the injured. Copyright PUNCH.
